             <p><lb n="1"/><unclear>na</unclear>mo bhaga<unclear>va</unclear>to <space/> budha<unclear>sa</unclear><gap reason="lost"/><lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost"/><unclear>to ca</unclear> tha<unclear>bho</unclear> be dam<unclear>u</unclear><supplied reason="lost">r</supplied><unclear>ī</unclear><gap reason="lost"/><lb n="3"/><gap reason="lost"/>kārapitaṁ <space/> sa<unclear>ṁ</unclear>gha<gap reason="lost"/><lb n="4"/><supplied reason="lost">sat</supplied><unclear>ike</unclear>na mahāsena<unclear>date</unclear><supplied reason="lost">na</supplied></p>
         </div>
         <div type="apparatus">
             <listApp>
                 <app loc="2">
                     <lem><unclear>to ca</unclear> tha<unclear>bho</unclear> be dam<unclear>u</unclear><supplied reason="lost">r</supplied><unclear>ī</unclear></lem>
                     <rdg source="bib:Nakanishi+Hinuber2014_01"><unclear>toda</unclear>thuthibadama</rdg>
                     <note>The tentative reading <foreign>dam<unclear>u</unclear><supplied reason="lost">r</supplied><unclear>ī</unclear></foreign> may be compared to <foreign>damurā</foreign>, occurring on several floor slabs from Kesanapalli, see <ref target="DHARMA_INSEIAD00231.xml">EIAD 231</ref>, <ref target="DHARMA_INSEIAD00233.xml">233</ref>, <ref target="DHARMA_INSEIAD00234.xml">234</ref>. The derivation of this term remains unclear.</note>
                 </app>
                 <app loc="4">
                     <lem><supplied reason="lost">sat</supplied><unclear>ike</unclear>na mahāsena<unclear>date</unclear><supplied reason="lost">na</supplied></lem>
                     <rdg source="bib:Nakanishi+Hinuber2014_01"><unclear>ke</unclear>na m<unclear>ā</unclear>hisa<unclear>kasa</unclear></rdg>
                     <note>My reconstruction is supported by <ref target="DHARMA_INSKnI00100.xml">KnI0100</ref> and by the fragment <ref target="DHARMA_INSKnI00292.xml">KnI0292</ref>, l. 2, reading <foreign>satikena ma<unclear>h</unclear></foreign>.</note>
                 </app>
